<akn:akomaNtoso xmlns:akn="http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0"><akn:act><akn:meta><akn:identification source="#cosilico"><akn:FRBRWork prescriptive="true" authoritative="true"><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/42/7384w" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" name="retrieval" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#us-congress" /><akn:FRBRcountry value="us" /></akn:FRBRWork><akn:FRBRExpression><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/42/7384w/eng@2025" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#cosilico" /><akn:FRBRlanguage language="en" /></akn:FRBRExpression><akn:FRBRManifestation><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/42/7384w/eng@2025/main.xml" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#cosilico" /></akn:FRBRManifestation></akn:identification></akn:meta><akn:body><akn:section eId="sec_7384w"><akn:num>7384w</akn:num><akn:heading>Subpoenas; oaths; examination of witnesses</akn:heading><akn:content><akn:p>§ 7384w. Subpoenas; oaths; examination of witnesses
The Secretary of Labor, with respect to any matter under this part, may—(1) issue subpoenas for and compel the attendance of witnesses;

(2) administer oaths;

(3) examine witnesses; and

(4) require the production of books, papers, documents, and other evidence.

(Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [div. C, title XXXVI, § 3632], as added Pub. L. 108–375, div. C, title XXXI, § 3163(a), Oct. 28, 2004, 118 Stat. 2186.)</akn:p></akn:content><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7384w_1"><akn:num>(1)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(1) issue subpoenas for and compel the attendance of witnesses;</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7384w_2"><akn:num>(2)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(2) administer oaths;</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7384w_3"><akn:num>(3)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(3) examine witnesses; and</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7384w_4"><akn:num>(4)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(4) require the production of books, papers, documents, and other evidence.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>